# Validation and CI

## Automated suites

| Command | Covers |
|---------|--------|
| `npm test` | `node --test` on `tests/js/**` + `npm run test:syntax` (glob `node --check` over all `.js` under `src/`) |
| `npm run test:python` | `tests/python/**` via `scripts/run-python-tests.js` |
| `npm run test:python-syntax` | Recursive `compileall` over `backend/` via `scripts/check_python_syntax.py` |
| `npm run test:all` | JS + Python unit tests + Python syntax — run before opening a PR |

CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`): JS + Python tests, recursive backend `compileall`, JS syntax checks, manifest tests, packaged-build smoke — not full E2E with real audio devices.

## When to add tests

- New pure helpers → `tests/js/` or `tests/python/` alongside existing patterns.
- Recorder stdout / IPC / cache semantics → update existing contract tests (`main-process-helpers`, `test_transcriber_helpers`, `ai-addon-*`).

## Manual checklists (hardware-dependent)

- Recorder pipeline: `tests/manual/recording-smoke-checklist.md`
- Local AI add-ons: `tests/manual/local-ai-addons-checklist.md`

Fresh machine setup: `docs/development/TESTING.md`.
